<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Honduras</gloss>
                                to Minister <persName type="to">Merry</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><placeName type="venue"><hi rend="smallcaps">Palace</hi></placeName>, <lb/>
                                    <placeName type="city"><hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-21"><hi rend="italic">July
                                        21, 1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Informed of the celebration of peace between El Salvador, Guatemala, and
                            Honduras, I have the satisfaction of congratulating you very sincerely
                            upon the part you have taken in the favorable result obtained. I also
                            request you to present to President Roosevelt the gratitude of the
                            Government and people of Honduras for his friendly and efficient
                            mediation in this affair.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Manuel Bonilla</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>